**What it does**
Doubles the `n` field of each incoming item and returns the result as `doubled`.

---

**Issues found**

- **Wrong variable name for input items**
  - **Node:** `Code`
  - **Problem:** The code references `items` directly, but in the Code node's default mode ("Run Once for All Items"), the correct variable to access incoming data is `$input.all()`. The bare `items` variable is not defined in the n8n sandbox, so the runtime throws a `ReferenceError: items is not defined`. [Code node common issues](https://docs.n8n.io/integrations/builtin/core-nodes/n8n-nodes-base.code/common-issues/)
  - **Fix:** Replace `items` with `$input.all()`:
    ```javascript
    const items = $input.all().map(i => ({ json: { doubled: i.json.n * 2 } }));
    return items;
    ```

- **Silent failure when `n` is missing or undefined**
  - **Node:** `Code`
  - **Problem:** The Manual Trigger emits one empty item (`{ json: {} }`) by default. `i.json.n` will be `undefined`, so `undefined * 2` produces `NaN`. The node won't throw, but the output will be `{ doubled: NaN }`, which is almost certainly not intended. [Code node common issues](https://docs.n8n.io/integrations/builtin/core-nodes/n8n-nodes-base.code/common-issues/)
  - **Fix:** Either supply test data via pinned data on the Manual Trigger, or add a guard:
    ```javascript
    const items = $input.all().map(i => ({
      json: { doubled: typeof i.json.n === 'number' ? i.json.n * 2 : null }
    }));
    return items;
    ```

---

**Summary of the corrected Code node**

```javascript
const items = $input.all().map(i => ({
  json: { doubled: typeof i.json.n === 'number' ? i.json.n * 2 : null }
}));
return items;
```

**Runtime things to verify after fixing**
- Pin test data on the Manual Trigger with at least one item containing `{ "n": <number> }` so the Code node has real input to work with.
- Confirm the output item structure is `[{ json: { doubled: ... } }]` — the Code node requires every returned element to have a `json` key pointing to a plain object, not an array or primitive. [Code node common issues](https://docs.n8n.io/integrations/builtin/core-nodes/n8n-nodes-base.code/common-issues/)
